          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 pt-4">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-3 bg-slate-500 text-white font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-lg">
              <span>127 Hours</span>
              <span>Tested</span>
            </span>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-3 bg-slate-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm text-slate-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-lg border border-slate-500/30">
              <span>3 Platforms</span>
              <span>Compared</span>
            </span>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-3 bg-slate-500/10 backdrop-blur-sm text-slate-200 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-lg border border-slate-500/20">
              <span>Agency</span>
              <span>Data</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE CASE STUDY -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="border-l-[3px] border-slate-500 pl-8 py-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">My Experience: The Agency That Lost $300K Waiting For Perfect</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">October 2024 | Austin, TX | Real agency case study</p>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-slate-300 pl-6 py-5 bg-slate-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-slate-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Forge Digital, design agency in Austin. Client sites ship on time. Their own site? Outdated 3 years, "redesign in progress" for 18 months. Problem: Custom build mentality paralyzed them. Perfect animations. Endless revisions. Meanwhile, losing $50K/month potential clients ("your agency looks stagnant"). Agency owner: "We're our own worst client. Every client site gets priority. Our site gets pushed to next month. Again." Revenue flat $180K/month for 2 years. Competitors launching fresh sites, winning work Forge should win.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-5 bg-gray-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">November 2, 2024 (1-day Framer build): Portfolio showcase with case studies prominently (12 projects with results metrics visible), services pages clear (Branding $30-50K, Web Design $20-40K, Strategy $15-25K), team bios with photos (humans, not faceless logo), client testimonials with results ("+340% leads"), inquiry form prominent (budget range checkboxes qualify leads), mobile-optimized (73% prospects browse phones). Budget: $1,200 (Framer $300 annual + copywriting freelancer $400 + 12 hours agency time @ $40/hr). ROI: Agency math different from products. Site generates leads = retainers worth $180-360K over 3 years.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-slate-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-slate-100 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-slate-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">February 2025 (3 months post-launch): Monthly inquiries increased from 8 to 22 (175% increase). Qualified leads (budget $30K+) increased from 3 to 12 (300% increase). Closed 4 new retainers: Branding $45K, Web $35K, Strategy $25K, ongoing retainer $18K/month. First-month revenue from new site: $123K. Recovering $300K lost in 6 months of "redesign in progress." Agency perception transformed: "Stagnant" ‚Üí "Forward-thinking." Competitor clients reaching out (saw fresh site, assume agency is current). Staff pride: "Finally proud to share our URL."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-gray-100 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-gray-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 3-MONTH BREAKDOWN</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Week 1 (November 4):</strong> Framer site launched. Portfolio reorganized (12 projects, each with results: "+340% leads," "18% conversion increase"). Services pricing transparent (clients self-select based on budget = qualified inquiries only). Month 1 inquiries: 12 (was 8), qualified leads: 6 (was 3). Closed 1 retainer $25K (Strategy - smaller, faster close). <strong>Month 2:</strong> Added case study PDF downloads (lead magnets: "Our Brand Process: 6 Weeks to Launch"). Month 2 inquiries: 18, qualified leads: 9. Closed 1 retainer $35K (Web Design). <strong>Month 3:</strong> Added client video testimonials (3 clients recorded 30-second clips: "Forge delivered our rebrand 6 weeks early"). Month 3 inquiries: 22, qualified leads: 12. Closed 2 retainers: Branding $45K (largest in agency history), ongoing retainer $18K/month. Staff morale: "Prospects compliment our site, finally proud to share URL." The transformation: Portfolio visible (results shown = confidence), pricing transparent (qualified self-select = saves time), testimonials social proof (clients vouch = trust). Agency site isn't portfolio. It's lead generation engine. Treat it like one.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-6xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">THE HARD TRUTH</h2>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-12">Your agency site shouldn't be your most complex project. It should be your fastest win.</p>

