        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-slate-300 p-6 shadow-lg">
          <p class="text-5xl font-black text-slate-500 mb-3">01</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">"Our Site Next Month" = Never</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Forge Digital: "Our site in progress" for 18 months. Custom build paralysis. Client sites ship. Agency site doesn't. Result: Lost $300K potential revenue (6 months √ó $50K/month leads). Competitors launched, won work Forge should have. Agencies treat their site differently: "Must be perfect." Reality: Good enough > perfect never. Ship fast, improve iteratively.</p>
        </div>

