        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-slate-400 pl-6 py-5 bg-slate-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-slate-800 mb-3">EMERGENCY RUSH CASE STUDY: SAVED CLIENT RELATIONSHIP</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">LaunchReady Agency, client called Friday 4pm: "Need site live by Monday morning. Conference booth. Emergency. Can you help?" Traditional timeline: 2 weeks minimum. Durable: Generated site in 30 seconds, edited content 5 minutes, client reviewed 30 minutes, revisions 1 hour. Total time: 2 hours. Site live Friday 6pm. Client: "You're geniuses. Conference was huge success, got 47 leads from site." Result: Client relationship saved (would have lost if missed deadline), upsold to custom build post-conference ($35K), referred 2 new clients ("LaunchReady delivered impossible, they'll deliver for you"). Durable wins for emergency rush: 30-second generation (unbeatable speed), built-in CRM (lead capture integrated), very easy for non-technical clients (edit themselves), PageSpeed 95+ (fast loading). But generic designs (all Durable sites look similar), no export (stuck in ecosystem), limited customization (can't match custom branding). Emergency button only, not primary builder.</p>
